    "body": "## Problem:\r\nThe `_watch.watch()` strategy may fail if the given path does not exist:\r\n\r\n    â€¦/vim/_watch.lua:101: ENOENT: no such file or directory\r\n    stack traceback:\r\n        [C]: in function 'assert'\r\n        â€¦/vim/_watch.lua:101: in function <â€¦/vim/_watch.lua:61>\r\n        [string \"<nvim>\"]:5: in main chunk\r\n\r\n- `_watch.watch()` actively asserts any error returned by `handle:start()`.\r\n- whereas `_watch.watchdirs()` just ignores the result of `root_handle:start()`.\r\n\r\nServers may send \"client/registerCapability\" with \"workspace/didChangeWatchedFiles\" item(s) (`baseUri`) which do not actually exist on the filesystem: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/28058#issuecomment-2189929424\r\n\r\n    {\r\n      method = \"client/registerCapability\",\r\n      params = {\r\n        registrations = { {\r\n            method = \"workspace/didChangeWatchedFiles\",\r\n            registerOptions = {\r\n              watchers = { {\r\n                  globPattern = {\r\n                    baseUri = \"file:///Users/does/not/exist\",\r\n                    pattern = \"**/*.{ts,js,mts,mjs,cjs,cts,json,svelte}\"\r\n                  }\r\n                },\r\n    ...\r\n    }\r\n\r\n## Solution:\r\n- Remove the assert in `_watch.watch()`.\r\n- Show a once-only message for both cases.\r\n- More detailed logging is blocked until we have `nvim_log` / `vim.log`.\r\n\r\nfix #28058",
    "closed_at": "2024-10-02T15:05:03Z",
